reviews.text:
we took the tsuen wan red line to admiralty then changed to the new green southern island line to lei tong in ap lei chau 鸭脷洲

ap lei chau is tiny island south of and connected to aberdeen by small congested waterway..

the waterway is beautiful especially at sunset!

we took ferry HK$2.50pax on left pier to aberdeen wholesale fish market..like tokyo’s tsukiji market which supplies most restaurants here..

27.5.2019
I've lived here for over 10 years. Great place surrounded by the sea. Good fengshui and now there is mtr connection.
Not much going on in here...

It is beautiful 👌
